<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,671,1350,1411]" box="[151,308,1385,1411]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,300,1385,1411]" captionStart="FIGURES 69–75" captionStartId="46.[151,269,1885,1909]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,198,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-70@46.[151,1436,194,1861]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 69–75. Leptocera gongylotheca sp.n. (Argentina). Male terminalia (phallus and postgonites omitted): (69) lateral; (70) posterior; (71) ventral; (72) sternite 5. Female terminalia: (73) dorsal; (74) spermathecae; (75) ventral. cp—finger-like process of cercus, da—desclerotized area, proc—process at base of posterior section of surstylus, sa—shining area of tergite 7." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5311894" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5311894/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Figs. 69–75</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1436,1462,2030]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,296,1462,1488]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Description</emphasis>
. Indistinguishable from 
<taxonomicName authority="Buck &amp; Marshall, 2009" authorityName="Buck &amp; Marshall" authorityYear="2009" box="[581,746,1463,1488]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Leptocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentinica" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis box="[581,746,1463,1488]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">L. argentinica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[752,807,1462,1488]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
except for the shape of the female spermathecae (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 69–75" captionStartId="46.[151,269,1885,1909]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,198,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-70@46.[151,1436,194,1861]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 69–75. Leptocera gongylotheca sp.n. (Argentina). Male terminalia (phallus and postgonites omitted): (69) lateral; (70) posterior; (71) ventral; (72) sternite 5. Female terminalia: (73) dorsal; (74) spermathecae; (75) ventral. cp—finger-like process of cercus, da—desclerotized area, proc—process at base of posterior section of surstylus, sa—shining area of tergite 7." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5311894" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5311894/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 74</figureCitation>
): Spermatheca perfectly spherical, lacking narrow, ridged, subcylindrical basal section; entire surface (except very base) bumpy. Male terminalia as in 
<figureCitation box="[722,864,1540,1566]" captionStart="FIGURES 69–75" captionStartId="46.[151,269,1885,1909]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,198,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-70@46.[151,1436,194,1861]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 69–75. Leptocera gongylotheca sp.n. (Argentina). Male terminalia (phallus and postgonites omitted): (69) lateral; (70) posterior; (71) ventral; (72) sternite 5. Female terminalia: (73) dorsal; (74) spermathecae; (75) ventral. cp—finger-like process of cercus, da—desclerotized area, proc—process at base of posterior section of surstylus, sa—shining area of tergite 7." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5311894" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5311894/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Figs. 69–72</figureCitation>
, female terminalia as in 
<figureCitation box="[1150,1292,1540,1566]" captionStart="FIGURES 69–75" captionStartId="46.[151,269,1885,1909]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,198,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-70@46.[151,1436,194,1861]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 69–75. Leptocera gongylotheca sp.n. (Argentina). Male terminalia (phallus and postgonites omitted): (69) lateral; (70) posterior; (71) ventral; (72) sternite 5. Female terminalia: (73) dorsal; (74) spermathecae; (75) ventral. cp—finger-like process of cercus, da—desclerotized area, proc—process at base of posterior section of surstylus, sa—shining area of tergite 7." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5311894" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5311894/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Figs. 73–75</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
